    "arbitrationType":  "mechanical",
    "aiContext":  {
                      "prompt":  "Resolve the target\u0027s Intelligence saving throw, treating immunity to Frightened as automatic success; on a failed save, randomize visible creature targets and offer the repeat Intelligence save whenever the target takes damage.",
                      "playerInputRequired":  true
                  },
    "description":  "You reach into the mind of one creature you can see and force it to make an Intelligence saving throw. A creature automatically succeeds if it is immune to being frightened. On a failed save, the target loses the ability to distinguish friend from foe, regarding all creatures it can see as enemies until the spell ends. Each time the target takes damage, it can repeat the saving throw, ending the effect on itself on a success. Whenever the affected creature chooses another creature as a target, it must choose the target at random from among the creatures it can see within range of the attack, spell, or other ability it\u0027s using. If an enemy provokes an opportunity attack from the affected creature, the creature must make that attack if it is able to.",
